'''Fakhreddine II Palace''' is a 17th-century [[palace]] in [[Deir el Qamar]]-[[Chouf District | Chouf]] in [[Lebanon]]. It was built by Emir [[Fakhr-al-Din II]] in the early 17th century. It houses the [[Marie Baz Museum]], a wax work museum.

