{{Infobox monument |monument_name = Memorial to the people killed by Bolsheviks |native_name = |image = |caption = |location = [[Răzeni]] |designer = [[Tudor Cataraga]] |type = |material = |length = |width = |height = |begin = |complete = 2009 |open = February 21, 2009 |dedicated_to = Victims of the [[Răzeni Massacre]] |map_image = |map_caption = |map_width = |coordinates = |lat = |long = |extra = }}
The '''Stone cross in the memory of the people killed by Bolsheviks''' ({{lang-ro|Crucea de piatră de la Rezeni în memoria celor omorâţi de bolşevici}}) is a [[monument]] in [[Răzeni]], [[Moldova]].
==Overview== The memorial is dedicated to the victims of the [[Răzeni Massacre]]. The massacre took place on June 22, 1941, in [[Răzeni]], when 10 people were killed by the [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] authorities and buried in a [[mass grave]].<ref>Dumitru Lazur, Omorâţi mișelește de bolșevici comuniști, [[Curierul Ortodox]], nr 6 (191), 15 June 2007.</ref> The memorial was opened on February 21, 2009; Moldovian [[politician]] [[Alexandru Tănase]] was present.
In 1941 after [[Operation Barbarossa]], when the area came under the control of the pro-[[Nazi]] [[Ion Antonescu|Antonescu]] regime, a commemorative plaque was installed in Răzeni: "Aici odihnesc robii lui Dumnezeu Diomid, Niculai, Dănila, Nichita, Alexandru, Jurian, Alexandru, Ilie, doi necunoscuţi. Omorâţi mișelește de bolșevici comuniști. 12.VII.1941".<ref>Dumitru Lazur, Omorâţi mișelește de bolșevici comuniști, [[Curierul Ortodox]], nr 6 (191), 15 June 2007.</ref>
==See also== *[[Mass killings under Communist regimes]]
